      <akn:section eId="sec_50_2301_05">
        <akn:num>50-2301.05</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Monetary sanctions and fees.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2301_05_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The maximum monetary sanctions that may be imposed under this chapter shall be as follows:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2301_05_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A respondent may pay such fines and penalties by use of credit cards approved by the Director.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2301_05_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Director may permit, in his or her sole discretion, persons owing substantial fines, fees or charges to the Department to pay the amounts owed in installments at intervals as the Director may decide; and</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_50-2301_05_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>The Director may collect a fee for the filing of an appeal pursuant to §  50-1404.02.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
